HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 140
BY REPRESENTATIVE HILFERTY
A RESOLUTION
To commend Freddy Yoder for more than thirty years of service with the Lakeview Civic
Improvement Association in New Orleans.
WHEREAS, it is most fitting to recognize Freddy Yoder for his dedication to the
Lakeview community and to commend him for more than thirty years of service with the
Lakeview Civic Improvement Association; and
WHEREAS, throughout Mr. Yoder's decades-long tenure with the Lakeview Civic
Improvement Association, he has inspired civic engagement and fostered unity,
volunteerism, and public service; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Yoder is an inspiring leader who champions infrastructure funding
and unites communities, businesses, and government to improve education, safety, and
development in the Lakeview neighborhood; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Yoder co-founded the Lakeview Crime Prevention District,
Louisiana's first crime prevention district; he also helped restore and beautify New Basin
Canal Park after Hurricane Katrina and transformed the area into a vibrant community space;
and
WHEREAS, Freddy Yoder is most deserving of the highest recognition for his
enduring contributions to Lakeview and its residents.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana does hereby commend Freddy Yoder for more than thirty years of
service with the Lakeview Civic Improvement Association in New Orleans and does hereby
encourage citizens to follow his incredible example of civic involvement and community
service.
SPEAKER OF THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
